---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Disclaimer and Terms of Use" description="How to use this reference and its templates: educational information only, not legal or compliance advice, provided without warranty. Independent and not affiliated with any regulator or standards body.">
  <header class="dc-hero">
    <div class="wrap dc-inner">
      <nav class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> <span>›</span> Disclaimer and Terms</nav>
      <h1 class="dc-h1">Disclaimer and Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="dc-lead">Please read this before you use the articles, templates, or downloadable documents on this site. Using the site means you accept these terms.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="wrap dc-body">
    <section>
      <h2>Educational information, not advice</h2>
      <p>This site is a free, independent educational reference on quality systems, data integrity, and validation in regulated life sciences. Everything on it, including articles, templates, checklists, and downloadable documents, is general information for learning and as a starting point. It is not legal, regulatory, compliance, medical, or other professional advice, and it does not create any professional relationship. Decisions about your products, processes, and compliance should be made with your own qualified personnel and, where appropriate, your own legal and regulatory advisers.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>No warranty, verify against the official source</h2>
      <p>The content is provided "as is," without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including accuracy, completeness, or fitness for a particular purpose. Regulations, guidances, and standards change, and interpretations differ. Always confirm any regulation, guidance, standard, citation, date, or technical detail against the current, official, published source, and against your own quality system, before you rely on it. Do not act on this site alone.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How this content is prepared, including AI assistance</h2>
      <p>This material is researched and drafted by the author with the assistance of AI tools, and then reviewed. AI-assisted text can contain errors, including a misstated requirement, an out-of-date position, or an incorrect citation. Treat everything here as a starting point, not a primary source. Confirm every regulation, guidance, standard, clause, date, figure, and citation against the current official published source, and apply your own professional judgment, before you act on it.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, the author is not liable for any loss, damage, regulatory outcome, or other consequence arising from use of this site or its documents. You use the site and its templates at your own risk.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Using the templates and documents</h2>
      <p>The templates and downloadable documents are generic starting points written in original wording. They are not a finished compliance solution. You are responsible for adapting each one to your own company, system, and process, completing every placeholder, having it reviewed and approved through your own document control, validating its use where required, and ensuring it meets the regulations that apply to you. Downloading or using a template does not create, prove, or guarantee compliance.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Independence</h2>
      <p>This site is independent and personal. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, sponsored by, or representing the FDA, EMA, MHRA, PIC/S, ISPE, PDA, USP, ISO, IEC, ICH, ASTM, any other regulator or standards body, or any employer. Any views are the author's own.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Citations, trademarks, and copyright</h2>
      <p>Regulations, guidances, and standards are referred to by their number, title, and publisher for identification and educational purposes only. Trademarks, product names, and standard names are the property of their respective owners and are used nominatively, with no claim of ownership or endorsement.</p>
      <p>Where regulatory text is quoted, it is quoted briefly and attributed, and is drawn from public sources such as the US Code of Federal Regulations and FDA guidance (US government works) and EU legislation. The site does not reproduce the copyrighted text of standards published by bodies such as ISO, IEC, USP, ISPE, or ASTM; those are described in original wording and referenced by citation only. To obtain the full text of any standard, purchase or access it from the publisher. If you believe any material infringes a copyright, contact the address below and it will be reviewed and addressed promptly.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Independently developed, original, non-confidential content</h2>
      <p>All content, including the articles, templates, and downloadable documents, is independently developed educational material based on publicly available information and general professional knowledge. It does not contain, and is not derived from, any confidential, proprietary, or trade secret information, internal procedure, document, dataset, template, risk methodology, or governance framework of any current or former employer, client, or other third party. All company names, systems, numbers, and examples are generic or fictional and are used only to illustrate a general principle. The views are the author's own and do not represent any employer, past or present.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>This is a static informational site. It does not require an account or login, it does not host contact or signup forms, and it does not set advertising or tracking cookies. It does not ask for or collect personal information from visitors. If you choose to email the address below, your message and email address are used only to respond to you. Basic aggregate traffic and security data may be processed by the site's hosting and content-delivery provider to operate and protect the site, governed by that provider's own terms.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Acceptance, changes, and governing law</h2>
      <p>By accessing or using this site you accept these terms. If you do not agree with them, do not use the site. These terms may be updated at any time without notice, and the version posted here governs your use. To the extent any dispute arises out of or relates to the site or its content, it is governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, United States, without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Open access</h2>
      <p>The articles and templates are free to read and to adapt for your own use. There is no paywall and no login.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions, corrections, or copyright concerns: <a href="mailto:goutham@madhadi.com">goutham@madhadi.com</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .dc-hero { background: var(--navy); color: #fff; }
  .dc-inner { padding: 3.2rem 0 2.4rem; }
  .crumb { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--on-navy-dim); margin-bottom: 1.1rem; } .crumb a { color: var(--on-navy-dim); } .crumb a:hover { color:#fff; } .crumb span { opacity:.6; margin:0 3px; }
  .dc-h1 { color: #fff; font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3.6vw, 2.8rem); margin: 6px 0 14px; letter-spacing: -0.025em; }
  .dc-lead { color: var(--on-navy); font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.5vw, 1.25rem); line-height: 1.5; max-width: 60ch; }
  .dc-body { max-width: var(--measure); padding: 48px 28px 60px; }
  .dc-body section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .dc-body h2 { font-family: var(--display); font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; padding-top: 1.2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .dc-body section:first-child h2 { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; }
  .dc-body p { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-2); margin-bottom: 0.9rem; }
  .dc-body a { color: var(--blue); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
